A N A C T
RELATING TO DELINQUENT AND DEPENDENT CHILDREN -- PROCEEDINGS IN
FAMILY COURT
Introduced By: Senators Tikoian, LaMountain, Gallo, DiPalma, Burke, Patalano,
McKenney, Dimitri, Paolino, and Raptakis
Date Introduced: May 09, 2025
Referred To: Senate Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 14-1-59 of the General Laws in Chapter 14-1 entitled "Proceedings
2 in Family Court" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 14-1-59. Cooperation of public and private agencies.
4 It is made the duty of every state, town, or municipal official or department, including, but
5 not limited to, the department of children, youth, and families, the department of health, the
6 department of human services, the department of elementary and secondary education, every school
7 district, the office of substance abuse, and the department of behavioral healthcare, developmental
8 disabilities and hospitals, to render all assistance and cooperation within his, her, or its jurisdictional
9 power which may further the objects of this chapter. All institutions or agencies providing services
10 to any child are required to give to the court any information concerning the child that the court
11 may require. The court is authorized to seek the cooperation of all societies or organizations having
12 for their object the protection or aid of children, and their physical or spiritual welfare; and the
13 court shall utilize the available services of all of those societies and organizations.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
